SIMPLE: thereupon
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Thereupon
<hw>There`up*on"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Upon that or this; thereon.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧They shall feed
<xex>thereupon</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Zeph. ii. 7.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>On account, or in consequence, of that;
therefore.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>[He] hopes to find you forward, . . . ⟦br⟧
And <qex>thereupon</qex> he sends you this good news.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Immediately; at once; without delay.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Therewhile</ent>⟦br⟧
